msgid "Subdivision"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:408
msgid ""
":menuselection:`Tool Shelf --> Tools --> Curve Tools --> Modeling: "
"Subdivide`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:409
msgid ":menuselection:`Curve --> Segments --> Subdivide`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:411
msgid ""
"Curve subdivision simply subdivides all selected segments by adding one "
"or more control points between the selected segments."
msgstr ""
"La subdivision de courbe subdivise simplement tous les segments "
"sélectionnés en ajoutant un ou plusieurs points de contrôle entre les "
"segments sélectionnés."

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:416
msgid "Number of Cuts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:415
msgid "The number of cuts can be adjusted from the Operator panel."
msgstr "le nombre de coupes peut être ajusté dans le panneau Operator."

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:421
msgid "Switch Direction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:427
msgid ""
":menuselection:`Tool Shelf --> Tools --> Curve Tools --> Curves: Switch "
"Direction`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:428
msgid ""
":menuselection:`Curve --> Segments --> Switch Direction`, "
":menuselection:`Specials --> Switch Direction`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:431
msgid ""
"This tool will \"reverse\" the direction of any curve with at least one "
"selected element (i.e. the start point will become the end one, and *vice"
" versa*). This is mainly useful when using a curve as path, or using the "
"bevel and taper options."
msgstr ""
"Cet outil va \"inverser\" la direction de toute courbe avec au moins un "
"élément sélectionné (càd. que le point de début va devenir le point de "
"fin, et *vice versa*). C'est utile principalement dans l'utilisation "
"d'une courbe comme chemin, ou l'utilisation des options *bevel* et "
"*taper*. "

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:439
msgid "Show/Hide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:441
msgid ""
"When in *Edit Mode*, you can hide and reveal elements from the display. "
"You can only show or hide control points, as segments are always shown, "
"unless all control points of the connected curve are hidden, in which "
"case the curve is fully hidden."
msgstr ""
"En *Mode Édition*, vous pouvez cacher et révéler des éléments de "
"l'affichage. Vous pouvez seulement afficher ou cacher les points de "
"contrôle, étant donné que les segments sont toujours affichés, à moins "
"que tous les points de contrôle de la courbe connectée soient cachés, "
"auquel cas la courbe est complètement cachée."

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:446
msgid ""
"See :ref:`object-show-hide` in *Object Mode*. See also the "
":doc:`/modeling/curves/curve_display` panel."
msgstr ""
"Voir :ref:`object-show-hide` en *Mode Objet*. Voir aussi le panneau "
":doc:`/modeling/curves/curve_display`."

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:453
msgid "Set Spline Type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:459
msgid ""
":menuselection:`Tool Shelf --> Tools --> Curve Tools --> Curves: Set "
"Spline type`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:464
msgid "Set Spline Type button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:466
msgid ""
"You can convert splines in a curve object between Bézier, NURBS, and Poly"
" curves. Press :kbd:`T` to bring up the Tool Shelf. Clicking on the *Set "
"Spline Type* button will allow you to select the Spline type (Poly, "
"Bézier or NURBS)."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez convertir des splines en un objet Courbe parmi les courbes de"
" Bézier, NURBS, et Poly. Pressez :kbd:`T` pour accéder au Tool Shelf. Le "
"clic sur le bouton *Set Spline Type* vous permettra de sélectionner le "
"type de Spline (Poly, Bézier or NURBS)."

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:470
msgid ""
"Note, this is not a \"smart\" conversion, i.e. Blender does not try to "
"keep the same shape, nor the same number of control points. For example, "
"when converting a NURBS to a Bézier, each group of three NURBS control "
"points become a unique Bézier one (center point and two handles)."
msgstr ""
"Notez que ce n'est pas une conversion \"intelligente\", càd. que Blender "
"ne cherche ni à garder la même forme, ni le même nombre de points de "
"contrôle. Par exemple, dans la conversion d'un NURBS en Bézier, chaque "
"groupe de trois points de contrôle NURBS devient un unique point Bézier "
"(un point central et deux poignées)"

